<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214036>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Aporcelaimellus tenuis sp. n. A: Anterior region in median view. B: Same in lateral, surface view. C: Male, entire body. D: Female, anterior genital branch. E: Pharyngeal expansion. F: Female, entire body. G: Male, posterior body region. H: Female, posterior body region. I: Spicule and lateral guiding piece. J: Vagina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/214036/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.214037>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Aporcelaimellus tenuis sp. n. (LM). A: Female, entire. B, C: Anterior region in median, lateral view. D: Lip region in surface, lateral view. E: Vagina. F: Female, bipartite uterus. G: Female, posterior body region. H: Dorsal cellular mass at anterior end of intestine. I: Pharyngo-intestinal junction. J: Male, lateral guiding pieces. K, L: Female, caudal region. M: Male, caudal region. N: Spicules. (Scale bars: A = 500 µm, B, I, N = 20 µm; C, E, K-M = 10 µm; D, J = 5 µm; F-H = 50 µm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/214037/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

